overview: The user's intent was to centralize and structure all requirements for
  a sleep questionnaire application. The assistant began by organizing existing
  documentation into a docs/correspondence directory and creating initial
  REQUIREMENTS.md and QUESTIONNAIRE_SPEC.md files. A key challenge was the
  presence of unreadable .docx and .pdf files. Following the user's instruction,
  the assistant successfully converted these binary files to text using
  command-line tools. The content from these newly readable files, particularly
  the detailed scoring and project scope, was then integrated into the
  REQUIREMENTS.md and QUESTIONNAIRE_SPEC.md documents, resulting in
  comprehensive and actionable documentation for the application.
